<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.5352.1.1>
    dc:creator "Jäger, Peter" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Revision of the huntsman spider genus Micrommata Latreille, 1804 (Sparassidae Sparassinae)" ;
    bibo:endPage "45" ;
    bibo:issue "1" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:pubDate "2023-10-02" ;
    bibo:startPage "1" ;
    bibo:volume "5352" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406890>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406933>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406935>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406942>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406944> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406890>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–3. Distribution ranges of Micrommata species. 1 M. virescens (red circles), M. diesenhoff spec. nov. (black triangle). 2 M.ligurina (red circles), M. biggi spec. nov. (black triangles).3 M. formosa (red circles), M.aljibica (black triangles). Majority of records is from specimens examined, some are from published literature or websites like iNaturalist (western record of M. aljibica, several records of M. virescens in its central range)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406890/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406933>
    dc:description "FIGURES 104–109. Micrommata virescens, male. 104–108 Left palp (104 prolateral; 105, 107 ventral; 106, 108 retrolateral). 109 Left chelicera, ventral (104–106 from Russia; 107–108 from Japan; 109 from Germany). E—embolus, EP—embolic plate, TP—tegular prong." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406933/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406935>
    dc:description "FIGURES 110–114. Micrommata virescens from Germany. 110–113 Prosoma with eye arrangement (110, 113 dorsal; 111 lateral; 112 frontal). 114 Left chelicera, ventral (110–112 male; 113–114 female)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406935/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406942>
    dc:description "FIGURES 129–132. Micrommata virescens, immatures from Germany, habitus (129, 132 juvenile; 130–131 subadult male)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406942/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8406944>
    dc:description "FIGURES 133–138. Micrommata virescens, adults from Germany, habitus and behaviour. 133 Male, looking for a female. 134 Female and male in the natural habitat. 135 Male and female in mating position. 136 Ditto, male bites leg of female. 137 Female with egg sac in rolled leaf of Rubus sp. 138 Egg sac with green eggs. Arrows indicating scars on the opisthosoma of female spiders. Photo credit: 136 Herbert Schirmer." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8406944/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

